Pre-Game Insights: Orlando Magic entered the game off a dramatic win against the New Orleans Pelicans, raising spirits within the team.
The Magic are looking to build momentum and maintain their home court dominance against the Washington Wizards.
The Wizards are struggling with a 2-5 record and are battling injuries, particularly with key players like Kyle Kuzma and Malcolm Brogdon out.
Orlando has historically performed well at home against Washington, winning five of their last six meetings.
Coach Jamahl Mosley has emphasized the importance of staying disciplined on defense to handle the Wizards' fast break.
